# Magic: The Gathering | Marvel Super Heroes \u8212? Collecting Knowledge Base\par
\par
Source article: Wizards of the Coast, \u8220?Collecting Magic: The Gathering\u174? | Marvel Super Heroes: The Four Most Important Things to Know,\u8221? published June 2, 2026.\par
\par
This file is a paraphrased, structured knowledge-base digest of the source page. It is not a verbatim copy of the article. Use it to answer questions about Magic: The Gathering | Marvel Super Heroes product contents, release timing, set codes, legality, Booster Fun treatments, booster collation, and prerelease contents.\par
\par
---\par
\par
## 1. Core Set Facts\par
\par
- Product line: Magic: The Gathering | Marvel Super Heroes.\par
- Tabletop release date: June 26, 2026.\par
- MTG Arena release date: June 23, 2026.\par
- Prerelease event window: June 19\u8211?25, 2026.\par
- Main set code: MSH.\par
- Commander set code: MSC.\par
- Source Material Cards set code: MAR.\par
- The set combines Magic gameplay with characters, locations, artwork, and stories from the Marvel Universe.\par
\par
### Legality\par
\par
- MSH cards are legal in all Magic formats.\par
- MSC and MAR are Eternal-legal sets: legal in Commander, Legacy, and Vintage.\par
- Individual MSC/MAR cards may also be legal in other formats where those cards are already legal.\par
- Play Boosters can contain cards from both MSH and MAR.\par
- Cards opened from Play Boosters are playable in Magic: The Gathering | Marvel Super Heroes Draft and Sealed.\par
