## 7. Practical Answering Guidance for a Custom GPT\par
\par
When answering questions using this KB:\par
\par
1. Distinguish between the set codes:\par
   - MSH = main set.\par
   - MSC = Commander / Eternal-legal related product cards.\par
   - MAR = Source Material Cards.\par
\par
2. For prerelease questions:\par
   - A prerelease pack contains six Play Boosters plus one traditional foil rare or mythic rare card.\par
   - The booster component should follow Play Booster collation, including land slots.\par
\par
3. For Play Booster simulations:\par
   - Include 14 Magic cards plus a helper/token card.\par
   - Include a land slot.\par
   - The land slot can produce common dual lands, default-frame basic lands, city calm basics, or city chaos basics.\par
   - Do not treat Play Boosters as having no lands.\par
\par
4. For Collector Booster questions:\par
   - Collector Boosters are the primary place for premium treatments such as classic comic cards, the Gauntlet Mind Stone, and the ultra-limited cosmic foil Mind Stone.\par
   - Every Collector Booster has a source material card slot.\par
\par
5. For Booster Fun treatment questions:\par
   - Classic comic cards: 15 mythic rare, foil-only, Collector Booster only, always English.\par
   - Source material cards: 60 total, including three Heroic Intervention versions; Play Boosters have them about 1 in 24, while Collector Boosters include one source material card.\par
   - Logo cards: 15 rare and 13 mythic rare, found in Play Boosters and Collector Boosters.\par
   - Scene cards: available across common/uncommon/rare/mythic, with multiple multi-card scenes.\par
   - Panel cards: 11 rare and 6 mythic rare.\par
   - Borderless lands: 5 rare dual lands with borderless versions.\par
\par
6. For product recommendation questions:\par
   - Play Boosters support Limited play and normal pack opening.\par
   - Collector Boosters focus on premium treatments and collector cards.\par
   - Jumpstart Boosters are for quick themed gameplay.\par
   - Commander Decks are ready-to-play Commander products.\par
   - Collector\u8217?s Edition Commander Decks are the premium surge-foil versions.\par
   - Scene Boxes are for collecting/displaying scene cards.\par
   - Beginner Box is for onboarding new players.\par
   - Draft Night provides a multi-player draft-oriented package with 12 Play Boosters and 1 Collector Booster.\par
